habitat_description:
The distribution of the pine woods treefrog only occurs along the Coastal Plain, southeast Virginia to south Florida and east Louisiana (Conant and Collins). They do not occur in in the Everglades and west to eastern Louisiana (Lannoo 2005).
Found high on trees, but also in lower levels even the ground. Associated with pine woods and cypress swamps (Bartlett and Bartlett 1999; Conant and Collins 1998). Also, hammocks, swamps, mixed hardwood/pine forests, and brackish marshes. Breeding takes place in swamps, depressional wetlands in pine flatwoods, vernal pools, Carolina bays, and other shallow water-filled depressions (Lannoo 2005).
